1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:07,864 --> 00:01:11,451
FOUR YEARS AGO

3
00:01:14,996 --> 00:01:15,914
EPISODE 3

4
00:01:15,997 --> 00:01:20,752
We own this entire orchard.

5
00:01:22,045 --> 00:01:23,046
I see.

6
00:01:27,342 --> 00:01:29,219
I thought my mom would be here.

7
00:01:30,053 --> 00:01:31,554
Maybe she's at the store.

8
00:01:31,638 --> 00:01:33,431
She runs a store as well.

9
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:39,479
I told you that our family
was influential in this town.

10
00:01:39,562 --> 00:01:40,814
Right.

11
00:02:04,379 --> 00:02:05,630
Mom!

12
00:02:07,799 --> 00:02:08,800
Mom?

13
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:10,552
YONGDU-RI SUPERMARKET

14
00:02:10,635 --> 00:02:11,678
Gosh.

15
00:02:11,761 --> 00:02:13,054
She's not here either.

16
00:02:20,854 --> 00:02:22,605
Pick whatever you want.

17
00:02:36,619 --> 00:02:37,745
Have this.

18
00:02:37,829 --> 00:02:39,122
It's a new flavor.

19
00:02:39,205 --> 00:02:40,540
ICE POP

20
00:02:41,457 --> 00:02:42,876
It's strawberry flavored.

21
00:02:42,959 --> 00:02:47,463
All the kids buy one after school
since it's so popular.

22
00:03:04,856 --> 00:03:06,232
It's good and refreshing.

23
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:07,942
It's my first time.

24
00:03:12,363 --> 00:03:14,574
It's your first time having an ice pop?

25
00:03:15,658 --> 00:03:18,536
Wait. Maybe not as an adult, but as a kid?

26
00:03:20,955 --> 00:03:23,374
Did your mom never buy you one?

27
00:03:24,334 --> 00:03:25,543
No, she didn't.

28
00:03:32,508 --> 00:03:35,637
To be honest, I kind of knew.

29
00:03:36,262 --> 00:03:37,096
Knew what?

30
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:40,225
You always wear t-shirts
with holes in them.

31
00:03:40,308 --> 00:03:41,517
What?

32
00:03:41,601 --> 00:03:43,519
That's vintage.

33
00:03:43,603 --> 00:03:46,648
-I got them made in Europe--
-What you're wearing today looks like

34
00:03:46,731 --> 00:03:48,650
something my grandma would wear.

35
00:03:48,733 --> 00:03:51,277
No, hear me out first.

36
00:03:51,361 --> 00:03:53,321
You'd be shocked to find out…

37
00:03:57,408 --> 00:03:59,077
the price of this cardigan.

38
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:01,704
-You don't have to pretend with me.
-Trust me.

39
00:04:02,372 --> 00:04:03,831
I'm not that poor.

40
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:06,626
Really.

41
00:04:08,544 --> 00:04:10,046
You should trust me instead.

42
00:04:10,129 --> 00:04:12,006
I give you my word.

43
00:04:13,508 --> 00:04:14,509
From this moment on,

44
00:04:14,592 --> 00:04:18,930
I'll let you enjoy
all the things you couldn't enjoy in life.

45
00:04:21,557 --> 00:04:22,934
That won't be easy.

46
00:04:23,017 --> 00:04:26,896
Didn't I tell you
that my apartment was leased?

47
00:04:26,980 --> 00:04:27,981
You did.

48
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,151
But there's more.

49
00:04:33,861 --> 00:04:34,862
To be honest…

50
00:04:39,867 --> 00:04:41,244
I save two million every month.

51
00:04:49,794 --> 00:04:52,130
Don't look at me
like you don't understand.

52
00:04:52,213 --> 00:04:53,423
I'm not bragging.

53
00:04:53,506 --> 00:04:55,091
I'm saying it's okay.

54
00:04:56,009 --> 00:04:58,928
I don't care if your family has debt.

55
00:05:02,056 --> 00:05:03,099
If we have debt?

56
00:05:05,018 --> 00:05:07,437
Even if there's more than that,

57
00:05:08,688 --> 00:05:09,856
I really don't care.

58
00:05:13,609 --> 00:05:14,610
Because…

59
00:05:16,112 --> 00:05:17,196
I'll be by your side.

60
00:05:21,117 --> 00:05:24,120
You'll be by my side?

61
00:05:24,203 --> 00:05:25,204
Yes.

62
00:05:26,539 --> 00:05:27,540
I'll be there

63
00:05:29,125 --> 00:05:30,335
for you.

64
00:05:36,341 --> 00:05:38,134
Why did this memory pop up?

65
00:05:42,597 --> 00:05:44,974
Would you be the last person on my mind

66
00:05:45,808 --> 00:05:48,269
if I died right now?

67
00:06:26,516 --> 00:06:27,517
Are you okay?

68
00:06:35,274 --> 00:06:36,442
Hae-in.

69
00:06:40,613 --> 00:06:41,906
Are you hurt?

70
00:06:44,617 --> 00:06:45,618
Are you okay?

71
00:06:46,202 --> 00:06:47,703
Can you wrap up here?

72
00:06:47,787 --> 00:06:49,372
She looks startled.

73
00:06:49,455 --> 00:06:50,998
She needs some rest.

74
00:06:55,253 --> 00:06:56,254
Let's go.

75
00:06:57,380 --> 00:06:58,381
Okay.

76
00:07:13,312 --> 00:07:15,356
It felt surreal at the hospital,

77
00:07:17,066 --> 00:07:19,277
but I really thought I'd die back there.

78
00:07:24,532 --> 00:07:26,200
So I told myself again

79
00:07:27,618 --> 00:07:29,912
that I would never die.

80
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:31,706
Because I felt

81
00:07:33,499 --> 00:07:34,625
offended.

82
00:07:40,590 --> 00:07:41,591
Are you okay?

83
00:07:47,597 --> 00:07:49,056
I think you sprained it.

84
00:08:02,153 --> 00:08:04,030
Am I being dramatic again?

85
00:08:07,116 --> 00:08:09,118
Yes, if this was any other day.

86
00:08:09,202 --> 00:08:10,786
But since I'm injured,

87
00:08:11,496 --> 00:08:13,498
I think it's reasonable.

88
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:16,959
Right?

89
00:08:30,223 --> 00:08:32,892
Isn't it easy to set wood on fire?

90
00:08:33,518 --> 00:08:35,019
But this is oak.

91
00:08:35,102 --> 00:08:37,522
-So is it impossible?
-No, it's not.

92
00:08:37,605 --> 00:08:40,775
But campers like me
prefer plum tree to oak.

93
00:08:40,858 --> 00:08:44,070
The burning smell of plum seeps
into the meat and makes it tasty.

94
00:08:44,862 --> 00:08:46,739
Okay. Go on then.

95
00:08:48,699 --> 00:08:51,118
Gosh, this makes me nostalgic.

96
00:08:51,786 --> 00:08:53,704
I'm reminded of when I went to Africa.

97
00:08:54,288 --> 00:08:58,793
My twenties were filled
with wildness and barbarism.

98
00:09:00,378 --> 00:09:01,629
You mean how you stayed

99
00:09:01,712 --> 00:09:04,757
in the hotel the whole week
due to the mosquitoes?

100
00:09:06,133 --> 00:09:08,844
I had enough of the wilderness
just looking out the window.

101
00:09:17,979 --> 00:09:19,105
What?

102
00:09:19,647 --> 00:09:21,857
-There's only smoke.
-Right.

103
00:09:21,941 --> 00:09:24,235
I think this wood is damp.

104
00:09:24,318 --> 00:09:27,280
Even the most skilled campers
can't do anything about this.

105
00:09:27,363 --> 00:09:29,574
Hyun-woo was never picky about wood.

106
00:09:30,908 --> 00:09:32,493
He's from the countryside.

107
00:09:32,577 --> 00:09:34,829
You can't compare me to him who probably

108
00:09:34,912 --> 00:09:37,415
played soccer
on unpaved roads with pig bladder.

109
00:09:37,498 --> 00:09:38,666
He has experience.

110
00:09:38,749 --> 00:09:41,502
Jeez, you and your excuses.

111
00:09:42,169 --> 00:09:43,879
Where is he, by the way?

112
00:09:43,963 --> 00:09:46,382
You can stop. Just ask him to do it.

113
00:09:46,465 --> 00:09:47,592
No, I can do it.

114
00:09:47,675 --> 00:09:50,136
Soo-cheol, that's enough. You can stop.

115
00:10:19,248 --> 00:10:20,416
Chamomile?

116
00:10:20,916 --> 00:10:21,959
Yes.

117
00:10:22,043 --> 00:10:25,087
Can you make two more
for the chairman and me?

118
00:10:26,505 --> 00:10:27,673
Sure.

119
00:10:27,757 --> 00:10:31,052
Why did Father return early
instead of hunting?

120
00:10:31,135 --> 00:10:32,094
Well…

121
00:10:32,178 --> 00:10:35,014
The great shaman contacted me.

122
00:10:35,097 --> 00:10:36,140
About what?

123
00:10:36,223 --> 00:10:39,393
The shaman suddenly asked
if the chairman had gone hunting.

124
00:10:39,477 --> 00:10:41,687
-How did she know?
-No wonder she's great.

125
00:10:42,647 --> 00:10:45,650
She said the chairman would be
in danger if he went hunting today.

126
00:10:46,901 --> 00:10:49,570
Is that why he came back right away?

127
00:10:49,654 --> 00:10:51,906
Yes, but at least
it's good news for Hae-in.

128
00:10:51,989 --> 00:10:53,366
She got to take his course.

129
00:10:54,575 --> 00:10:58,287
Mom!

130
00:10:59,413 --> 00:11:00,456
Hae-in got injured.

131
00:11:00,539 --> 00:11:01,540
What? How?

132
00:11:01,624 --> 00:11:04,043
I heard she met a boar while hunting.

133
00:11:04,126 --> 00:11:07,421
But her injuries
aren't that bad. They're not bad.

134
00:11:07,505 --> 00:11:09,548
Goodness. Is she okay?

135
00:11:14,053 --> 00:11:16,347
How did you know?

136
00:11:17,056 --> 00:11:18,265
You truly are the best.

137
00:11:22,103 --> 00:11:23,187
What did she say?

138
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:26,857
Anyway, thank you so much.
I'll visit you sometime soon.

139
00:11:28,275 --> 00:11:30,111
What did she say?

140
00:11:34,865 --> 00:11:37,660
Your ex-wife appeared in her dream.

141
00:11:37,743 --> 00:11:39,912
She was holding a knife
at a hunting ground.

142
00:11:39,995 --> 00:11:42,331
She wanted to take you with her.

143
00:11:42,415 --> 00:11:45,793
You could've been in grave danger
had you hunted today.

144
00:11:47,378 --> 00:11:48,337
See?

145
00:11:48,421 --> 00:11:50,172
You were wise to listen to me and return.

146
00:11:56,303 --> 00:11:58,723
Don't ignore superstitions.

147
00:11:58,806 --> 00:12:01,934
Check in with the shaman
before making big decisions.

148
00:12:02,017 --> 00:12:03,519
Okay.

149
00:12:14,739 --> 00:12:16,657
Shouldn't we call Doctor Kim?

150
00:12:16,741 --> 00:12:19,618
I'm okay. I just sprained it.

151
00:12:19,702 --> 00:12:21,537
Hyun-woo saved your life.

152
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:24,498
I thought he couldn't even shoot a bird,
but a boar?

153
00:12:24,582 --> 00:12:26,208
He was pretending all along.

154
00:12:26,292 --> 00:12:28,169
He probably has experience.

155
00:12:30,045 --> 00:12:32,715
Did you just compliment him?

156
00:12:32,798 --> 00:12:35,092
You need a lot of experience to catch one.

157
00:12:35,176 --> 00:12:38,137
Boars are thick-skinned,
so you need to hit the right spot.

158
00:12:38,220 --> 00:12:39,930
If not, it could be even more dangerous.

159
00:12:40,014 --> 00:12:45,186
Exactly. Thank God he was lucky.
What if he missed?

160
00:12:47,438 --> 00:12:49,231
Think about it.

161
00:12:49,315 --> 00:12:52,651
He shouldn't have been
so reckless as a rookie.

162
00:12:52,735 --> 00:12:55,571
He was a marine in the Special Guard Team.

163
00:12:55,654 --> 00:12:57,406
-He was known for his shooting.
-Really?

164
00:12:58,157 --> 00:12:59,784
Yes, really.

165
00:12:59,867 --> 00:13:02,161
Do you finally understand
how much of a fool you were

166
00:13:02,244 --> 00:13:04,079
to offer to teach him how to shoot?

167
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:07,666
One thing is for certain.

168
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:11,253
I wouldn't be here right now
had he hesitated even a bit.

169
00:13:15,299 --> 00:13:16,675
You lucky brat.

170
00:13:16,759 --> 00:13:19,428
-What?
-I could tell by his muscular arms

171
00:13:20,346 --> 00:13:23,933
that he didn't spend all his years
only studying.

172
00:13:24,016 --> 00:13:25,017
How could you tell?

173
00:13:26,018 --> 00:13:27,603
When I was in jail,

174
00:13:27,686 --> 00:13:30,397
he handed me the agreement
with those muscular arms

175
00:13:30,481 --> 00:13:32,358
and said, "Please sign this."

176
00:13:33,442 --> 00:13:34,610
And my heart

177
00:13:35,486 --> 00:13:36,487
fluttered.

178
00:13:36,570 --> 00:13:38,155
-Aunt.
-Aunt, come on.

179
00:13:42,660 --> 00:13:45,454
You amaze me at times, Hyun-woo.

180
00:13:45,538 --> 00:13:47,873
How did you make that decision
in that brief moment?

181
00:13:47,957 --> 00:13:49,917
I wasn't thinking.

182
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,086
It was instinctive.

183
00:13:52,169 --> 00:13:55,548
Your instincts knew
that you shouldn't let her die.

184
00:13:55,631 --> 00:13:59,677
You had to save her
so she'd revise her will. Right?

185
00:14:01,762 --> 00:14:02,888
Hello?

186
00:14:23,534 --> 00:14:24,535
Where's Hae-in?

187
00:14:25,327 --> 00:14:27,037
She took some meds and went to bed.

188
00:14:27,121 --> 00:14:28,998
She must've been so startled.

189
00:14:29,081 --> 00:14:31,000
I can't believe this.

190
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:34,295
Actually, I scanned the course earlier.

191
00:14:34,378 --> 00:14:36,672
I noticed that the fence was pried open.

192
00:14:36,755 --> 00:14:40,134
I believe the injured boar
had entered through that hole.

193
00:14:40,217 --> 00:14:43,053
That was supposed to be
Chairman Hong's course.

194
00:14:44,138 --> 00:14:45,639
What are you getting at?

195
00:14:46,432 --> 00:14:50,603
Are you saying someone purposely lured
the injured boar to harm him?

196
00:14:50,686 --> 00:14:52,855
We wouldn't know
even if that was the case.

197
00:14:55,566 --> 00:14:59,194
I'll check the nearby CCTV cameras
and dashcams.

198
00:14:59,862 --> 00:15:01,280
I'll check them myself.

199
00:15:01,363 --> 00:15:03,407
Would you like to do that?

200
00:15:03,908 --> 00:15:05,743
Okay, I'll get them ready.

201
00:15:05,826 --> 00:15:07,286
I'm sorry

202
00:15:07,369 --> 00:15:10,998
this had to happen
during your visit, Mr. Yoon.

203
00:15:11,081 --> 00:15:12,666
Don't worry about it, sir.

204
00:15:13,292 --> 00:15:14,960
Mr. Yoon, try the soup.

205
00:15:15,044 --> 00:15:16,795
I caught that pheasant.

206
00:15:18,213 --> 00:15:21,383
Come on. Don't lie, Dad.

207
00:15:22,384 --> 00:15:24,219
We bought them at a nearby farm.

208
00:15:28,223 --> 00:15:29,683
All right. Let's eat.

209
00:15:29,767 --> 00:15:30,809
Eat up.

210
00:15:40,277 --> 00:15:41,320
Thank you.

211
00:15:58,420 --> 00:16:00,339
Why did you season the bellflower roots?

212
00:16:00,881 --> 00:16:03,801
Hyun-woo prefers them charbroiled.

213
00:16:03,884 --> 00:16:05,552
No, I like this too.

214
00:16:06,428 --> 00:16:07,429
Really?

215
00:16:07,513 --> 00:16:08,889
Yes.

216
00:16:09,848 --> 00:16:11,183
Eat up.

217
00:16:11,266 --> 00:16:12,726
Yes, sir.

218
00:16:16,063 --> 00:16:17,064
Mr. Yoon.

219
00:16:17,147 --> 00:16:18,524
These are lacquer leaves.

220
00:16:18,607 --> 00:16:20,567
They're pretty rare.

221
00:16:20,651 --> 00:16:23,570
The mountain-bred ones
are very tasty and hard to find.

222
00:16:23,654 --> 00:16:25,072
I had them when I was younger.

223
00:16:25,155 --> 00:16:26,198
"Younger"?

224
00:16:27,282 --> 00:16:29,576
Didn't you grow up in the US?

225
00:16:29,660 --> 00:16:33,580
No, I went there when I was 13 years old.
I was in Korea up until then.

226
00:16:34,373 --> 00:16:37,334
Did your family immigrate there
or were you studying abroad?

227
00:16:37,418 --> 00:16:38,961
I was adopted overseas.

228
00:16:39,044 --> 00:16:42,339
My adoptive parents passed away
right before I graduated university.

229
00:16:43,090 --> 00:16:45,426
So I have no family now.

230
00:16:46,677 --> 00:16:49,638
I lost my parents at 15.

231
00:16:49,722 --> 00:16:52,016
And I came this far by myself.

232
00:16:52,099 --> 00:16:54,184
I wasn't aware of your family history.

233
00:16:54,935 --> 00:16:57,771
You're unlike today's young generation.

234
00:16:57,855 --> 00:16:58,897
I agree.

235
00:16:58,981 --> 00:17:01,525
I'm proud of you as if I'm your mother.

236
00:17:02,109 --> 00:17:06,238
Feel free to consider us
your Korean family.

237
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:07,990
I appreciate that.

238
00:17:08,073 --> 00:17:09,241
Eat up.

239
00:17:14,580 --> 00:17:16,248
Come here. Yes, over here.

240
00:17:19,752 --> 00:17:20,753
Thank you.

241
00:17:22,629 --> 00:17:24,673
Is he a Pungsan dog?

242
00:17:24,757 --> 00:17:25,966
Yes, sir.

243
00:17:26,050 --> 00:17:28,218
He's a handsome one.

244
00:17:28,302 --> 00:17:29,845
Not only is he handsome,

245
00:17:29,928 --> 00:17:33,474
but he saved my son years back
when our house was on fire.

246
00:17:33,557 --> 00:17:34,683
-Is that so?
-Yes, sir.

247
00:17:34,767 --> 00:17:36,185
My son was home alone.

248
00:17:36,268 --> 00:17:38,979
He would've lost his life
had our dog not woken him up

249
00:17:39,063 --> 00:17:40,522
and dragged him outside.

250
00:17:41,940 --> 00:17:45,611
He's intelligent and loyal.

251
00:17:47,654 --> 00:17:49,907
Would you be willing to sell him?

252
00:17:51,366 --> 00:17:52,826
Well…

253
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:53,911
I'm sorry, sir.

254
00:17:55,079 --> 00:17:56,455
He's family.

255
00:18:08,550 --> 00:18:11,095
-I'll give you 100 million.
-Sorry?

256
00:18:17,434 --> 00:18:20,562
But he doesn't even have a pedigree.

257
00:18:20,646 --> 00:18:21,730
That doesn't matter.

258
00:18:21,814 --> 00:18:23,440
I'll offer less with time.

259
00:18:26,693 --> 00:18:27,986
Ninety million.

260
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:43,001
-Eighty million.
-Wait.

261
00:18:43,085 --> 00:18:44,294
Honey.

262
00:18:44,795 --> 00:18:46,004
I'll sell him.

263
00:18:46,088 --> 00:18:47,548
But…

264
00:18:47,631 --> 00:18:49,258
could you give us 100 million?

265
00:18:51,969 --> 00:18:53,095
Sure.

266
00:19:09,778 --> 00:19:10,946
Honey.

267
00:19:11,029 --> 00:19:13,407
There's only one thing I don't have.

268
00:19:13,490 --> 00:19:14,867
It's prejudice, right?

269
00:19:14,950 --> 00:19:15,868
But what about it?

270
00:19:16,827 --> 00:19:18,203
It's about Mr. Yoon.

271
00:19:18,287 --> 00:19:22,624
Doesn't he seem too laidback for someone
who has gone through so much in life?

272
00:19:22,708 --> 00:19:24,960
He must've worked hard to make up for it.

273
00:19:25,043 --> 00:19:26,461
Don't judge a book by its cover.

274
00:19:26,545 --> 00:19:29,298
You can never know
what someone's thinking deep down.

275
00:19:29,381 --> 00:19:30,757
Are you sure you're from the US?

276
00:19:30,841 --> 00:19:34,469
You know our language and Korean proverbs
better than me.

277
00:19:34,553 --> 00:19:35,804
I already told you.

278
00:19:35,888 --> 00:19:40,100
My father made us only speak Korean
and read Korean books at home.

279
00:19:40,809 --> 00:19:41,810
What a wise man.

280
00:19:41,894 --> 00:19:44,646
Not everyone can become
an Ivy League professor.

281
00:19:46,315 --> 00:19:47,357
Would you like some?

282
00:19:50,861 --> 00:19:53,530
Right. Even beer is too bitter for you.

283
00:19:58,744 --> 00:20:02,247
You know I feel terrible that
I can't be your drinking buddy, right?

284
00:20:02,331 --> 00:20:04,708
What do you mean? Don't feel bad.

285
00:20:04,791 --> 00:20:05,834
I need the toilet.

286
00:20:21,475 --> 00:20:22,643
He's so chatty.

287
00:20:34,404 --> 00:20:36,573
Your room is the very last one
on the second floor.

288
00:20:38,116 --> 00:20:39,952
Yes, I know.

289
00:20:40,035 --> 00:20:41,328
Have a lovely night.

290
00:20:42,496 --> 00:20:43,664
You should go upstairs.

291
00:20:44,790 --> 00:20:46,041
I will.

292
00:20:46,124 --> 00:20:47,167
Good night then.

293
00:20:48,877 --> 00:20:49,920
Right, Soo-cheol.

294
00:20:52,923 --> 00:20:54,508
You asked me for advice last time

295
00:20:55,008 --> 00:20:57,719
on how to get
on the KFTC members' good side

296
00:20:57,803 --> 00:20:59,137
when they summoned you.

297
00:20:59,221 --> 00:21:00,347
Right.

298
00:21:01,515 --> 00:21:02,641
What do you say?

299
00:21:02,724 --> 00:21:05,477
Do you want some detailed tips right now?

300
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:06,561
Right now?

301
00:21:07,479 --> 00:21:11,733
Based on the legal expertise I obtained
during my law school days at SNU

302
00:21:11,817 --> 00:21:15,529
and years of working at the Legal Team,

303
00:21:15,612 --> 00:21:19,825
I could offer an extensive
yet simple explanation.

304
00:21:20,701 --> 00:21:24,329
I'm free from now
until late into the night.

305
00:21:25,372 --> 00:21:27,124
I'm not. My wife is waiting for me.

306
00:21:28,417 --> 00:21:29,668
Really? What a shame.

307
00:21:31,336 --> 00:21:34,089
I mean, it's a shame for you.

308
00:21:34,923 --> 00:21:36,550
This is a great opportunity.

309
00:21:41,179 --> 00:21:42,222
Are you afraid?

310
00:21:43,724 --> 00:21:44,891
Of what?

311
00:21:46,059 --> 00:21:47,728
Sleeping in the same room as Hae-in.

312
00:22:00,365 --> 00:22:01,533
Soo-cheol.

313
00:22:02,492 --> 00:22:04,161
That's absurd.

314
00:22:04,703 --> 00:22:05,746
We're married.

315
00:22:05,829 --> 00:22:08,790
Why would I be afraid
of sleeping next to my wife?

316
00:22:08,874 --> 00:22:10,042
All right.

317
00:22:15,297 --> 00:22:17,424
Where are you going?
Your room is up there.

318
00:22:21,303 --> 00:22:22,346
I know.

319
00:22:26,683 --> 00:22:27,768
Go straight.

320
00:22:31,938 --> 00:22:33,357
I truly

321
00:22:35,025 --> 00:22:36,026
pity him.

322
00:22:47,871 --> 00:22:50,582
-Where's the alcohol?
-What do you mean?

323
00:22:50,665 --> 00:22:52,167
You drank it all.

324
00:22:53,001 --> 00:22:54,044
I did?

325
00:22:54,127 --> 00:22:55,504
Are you drunk already?

326
00:22:56,088 --> 00:22:57,381
How cute.

327
00:22:58,882 --> 00:23:00,342
-Let's go to bed.
-Okay.

328
00:23:03,261 --> 00:23:05,055
I drank it all.

329
00:23:45,554 --> 00:23:46,680
What took you so long?

330
00:23:48,014 --> 00:23:49,433
Were you not sleeping?

331
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:51,518
I woke up.

332
00:23:53,854 --> 00:23:55,147
I asked you a question.

333
00:23:56,815 --> 00:23:57,691
Right.

334
00:23:58,442 --> 00:24:01,403
Soo-cheol asked me something,
so we were talking.

335
00:24:01,486 --> 00:24:02,571
What?

336
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:04,865
That lunatic.

337
00:24:05,699 --> 00:24:07,492
Was he pestering you at this hour?

338
00:24:09,077 --> 00:24:10,495
Honey. Hae-in.

339
00:24:11,121 --> 00:24:14,708
Please don't be so hot-tempered.

340
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:17,377
Should I go back out there

341
00:24:18,003 --> 00:24:20,630
and give him a stern warning?

342
00:24:20,714 --> 00:24:21,840
That's okay.

343
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:26,470
Right? That's what I thought.

344
00:24:26,553 --> 00:24:27,929
-Help me take off my top.
-What?

345
00:24:28,430 --> 00:24:31,308
I think I sprained my fingers.
It hurts to unbutton it.

346
00:24:31,933 --> 00:24:32,934
Can you do it?

347
00:24:38,815 --> 00:24:40,150
-Me?
-Yes.

348
00:24:41,026 --> 00:24:44,237
-Unbutton you?
-Yes, back here.

349
00:24:44,321 --> 00:24:45,322
Here.

350
00:25:03,006 --> 00:25:04,090
That's enough.

351
00:25:04,591 --> 00:25:06,927
I can do the rest.

352
00:25:07,552 --> 00:25:08,803
Okay.

353
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:11,681
Right.

354
00:25:21,691 --> 00:25:23,026
Why aren't you undressing?

355
00:25:23,109 --> 00:25:23,944
Do I have to?

356
00:25:26,112 --> 00:25:27,572
You're not showering?

357
00:25:28,323 --> 00:25:29,324
Do I have to?

358
00:25:43,672 --> 00:25:45,173
Should I not go out?

359
00:26:02,816 --> 00:26:03,817
What's wrong with you?

360
00:26:04,484 --> 00:26:07,112
Don't glamorize him.
He wasn't that handsome.

361
00:26:23,712 --> 00:26:24,754
Are you okay?

362
00:26:25,797 --> 00:26:27,674
No. Stop it.

363
00:26:27,757 --> 00:26:30,260
Don't replay it in slow motion.

364
00:26:35,890 --> 00:26:37,017
Don't do it.

365
00:26:38,101 --> 00:26:39,144
Don't.

366
00:26:53,658 --> 00:26:55,869
I couldn't find

367
00:26:56,536 --> 00:26:57,579
a bathrobe.

368
00:27:02,542 --> 00:27:03,543
Right.

369
00:27:04,377 --> 00:27:05,378
I see.

370
00:27:57,305 --> 00:27:58,431
I'm so dumbfounded.

371
00:28:00,308 --> 00:28:01,393
Does he think

372
00:28:02,811 --> 00:28:03,812
he's sexy?

373
00:28:04,354 --> 00:28:08,692
What in the world
happened to his body?

374
00:28:12,654 --> 00:28:14,489
Seriously.

375
00:28:30,088 --> 00:28:32,048
What? What do you want?

376
00:28:32,132 --> 00:28:33,133
I…

377
00:28:34,801 --> 00:28:37,095
There's a lot of water on the floor.

378
00:28:39,347 --> 00:28:41,933
You don't like that,
so I was going to wipe it.

379
00:28:43,393 --> 00:28:44,394
It's okay.

380
00:28:45,103 --> 00:28:46,229
Just go dry your hair.

381
00:28:49,232 --> 00:28:50,233
Don't tell me…

382
00:28:52,277 --> 00:28:54,362
you didn't dry your hair

383
00:28:54,446 --> 00:28:56,531
because you looked in the mirror

384
00:28:56,614 --> 00:28:59,242
and thought you looked like

385
00:28:59,325 --> 00:29:02,537
a drenched Timothée Chalamet
or a young Leonardo DiCaprio.

386
00:29:04,497 --> 00:29:05,665
What do you mean?

387
00:29:06,291 --> 00:29:07,500
If that's not why,

388
00:29:08,877 --> 00:29:10,170
then go dry your hair.

389
00:29:11,796 --> 00:29:12,797
Okay.

390
00:29:13,506 --> 00:29:14,507
I will.

391
00:29:22,182 --> 00:29:23,516
Unbelievable.

392
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:25,059
Was he trying to seduce me?

393
00:29:30,565 --> 00:29:31,566
I'm too stimulated

394
00:29:32,817 --> 00:29:33,985
for this hour.

395
00:29:54,631 --> 00:29:55,632
Are you sleeping?

396
00:30:01,054 --> 00:30:02,263
Not yet.

397
00:30:03,181 --> 00:30:05,391
The bed is small.

398
00:30:07,477 --> 00:30:08,853
Is this queen-sized?

399
00:30:08,937 --> 00:30:09,979
It's king.

400
00:30:10,063 --> 00:30:10,897
I see.

401
00:30:13,441 --> 00:30:15,068
It feels too small

402
00:30:16,402 --> 00:30:17,612
to be king-sized.

403
00:30:17,695 --> 00:30:18,947
There was a time

404
00:30:20,615 --> 00:30:22,116
when we slept together

405
00:30:22,992 --> 00:30:24,577
on a single bed.

406
00:30:26,329 --> 00:30:27,372
When?

407
00:30:28,581 --> 00:30:29,582
Don't you remember?

408
00:30:30,750 --> 00:30:32,252
My first visit to Yongdu-ri.

409
00:30:37,549 --> 00:30:40,593
CERTIFICATE OF AWARD
DILIGENCE AWARD

410
00:30:58,403 --> 00:31:00,822
Spend the night here.

411
00:31:14,335 --> 00:31:16,254
It's too late.

412
00:31:19,841 --> 00:31:21,342
It's 9:00 p.m.

413
00:31:21,426 --> 00:31:24,345
That's pretty late.

414
00:31:25,471 --> 00:31:27,599
-It's dangerous to drive at night.
-That's true.

415
00:31:27,682 --> 00:31:28,683
Right.

416
00:31:30,977 --> 00:31:32,061
Sleep here.

417
00:31:32,145 --> 00:31:34,606
I'll be in that room.

418
00:31:36,065 --> 00:31:37,775
I'll be there

419
00:31:38,651 --> 00:31:40,278
if you need me.

420
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:43,281
Good night then.

421
00:32:35,792 --> 00:32:37,377
The moon looked pretty.

422
00:32:39,295 --> 00:32:41,214
Maybe we could look at it together.

423
00:32:45,176 --> 00:32:46,177
Come in…

424
00:32:49,180 --> 00:32:50,264
if you want.

425
00:33:23,297 --> 00:33:24,549
-By the way…
-Yes?

426
00:33:25,299 --> 00:33:27,468
How did we even sleep

427
00:33:29,429 --> 00:33:30,471
on that bed?

428
00:33:31,264 --> 00:33:32,515
We cuddled.

429
00:33:33,433 --> 00:33:34,434
Right.

430
00:33:35,059 --> 00:33:36,060
Did we cuddle?

431
00:33:37,061 --> 00:33:39,689
Do you want to cuddle
if the bed is too small?

432
00:33:43,401 --> 00:33:45,570
I'm okay.

433
00:33:46,487 --> 00:33:47,530
It's not too small.

434
00:33:48,406 --> 00:33:49,949
I have some room.

435
00:33:53,411 --> 00:33:54,704
-Really?
-Yes.

436
00:33:55,246 --> 00:33:56,205
Then…

437
00:33:59,917 --> 00:34:01,169
do you want to cuddle

438
00:34:02,253 --> 00:34:03,421
nonetheless?

439
00:34:19,437 --> 00:34:20,396
I'm just kidding.

440
00:34:22,899 --> 00:34:23,900
Don't be so scared.

441
00:35:09,612 --> 00:35:10,947
What are you doing here?

442
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:13,324
Goodness.

443
00:35:13,407 --> 00:35:15,034
I'm sorry.

444
00:35:15,118 --> 00:35:17,912
I wasn't in my right mind yesterday.

445
00:35:20,248 --> 00:35:21,415
I'd like to give this back.

446
00:35:21,499 --> 00:35:24,043
Please help us.
We couldn't sleep last night.

447
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:29,841
I already gifted the dog to him,
so I can't do that.

448
00:35:29,924 --> 00:35:31,592
I'm sorry.

449
00:35:31,676 --> 00:35:34,428
He's family to us since he saved our son.

450
00:35:34,512 --> 00:35:37,557
I must've been insane
to have sold him.

451
00:35:38,391 --> 00:35:39,851
All right. I'll take this.

452
00:35:39,934 --> 00:35:41,811
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

453
00:35:41,894 --> 00:35:43,813
Thank you so much, sir.

454
00:35:43,896 --> 00:35:44,981
Goodness.

455
00:35:45,064 --> 00:35:45,982
What are you doing?

456
00:35:46,941 --> 00:35:48,442
You felt guilty for selling him.

457
00:35:51,279 --> 00:35:52,572
So let's just kill him off.

458
00:35:53,447 --> 00:35:54,574
Would that be better?

459
00:35:56,284 --> 00:35:57,702
What are you doing?

460
00:36:06,711 --> 00:36:08,713
Jeez, I almost shot you again.

461
00:36:12,633 --> 00:36:13,634
I asked you a question.

462
00:36:15,887 --> 00:36:17,138
I was just joking.

463
00:36:19,140 --> 00:36:20,641
Was that a joke to you?

464
00:36:20,725 --> 00:36:22,351
What do you think it was?

465
00:36:26,731 --> 00:36:28,024
Did you return the money?

466
00:36:29,984 --> 00:36:31,068
Did you get it?

467
00:36:32,195 --> 00:36:33,529
I'm your witness.

468
00:36:35,239 --> 00:36:36,407
The deal has ended.

469
00:36:42,705 --> 00:36:43,706
You may go.

470
00:36:44,290 --> 00:36:47,793
Thank you. Let's go.

471
00:36:48,669 --> 00:36:49,962
-Hurry.
-By the way,

472
00:36:51,672 --> 00:36:52,673
why can't I kill it?

473
00:36:53,549 --> 00:36:54,842
You heard him.

474
00:36:54,926 --> 00:36:56,010
He doted on the dog.

475
00:36:56,677 --> 00:36:58,304
The dog is like family.

476
00:36:58,387 --> 00:36:59,472
I see.

477
00:37:00,223 --> 00:37:04,060
In that case, is it okay
to kill abandoned or stray dogs?

478
00:37:26,374 --> 00:37:28,751
That's the entrance to the forest.

479
00:37:29,752 --> 00:37:32,463
No one else entered except for our family.

480
00:37:32,546 --> 00:37:36,008
Does that mean this was an inside job?

481
00:37:38,386 --> 00:37:39,220
Hold on.

482
00:37:46,894 --> 00:37:48,145
Stop there.

483
00:37:54,819 --> 00:37:55,820
Who is that?

484
00:37:55,903 --> 00:37:57,363
I can only see his back.

485
00:37:57,446 --> 00:37:58,489
That's your brother.

486
00:38:02,034 --> 00:38:02,994
That can't be.

487
00:38:03,077 --> 00:38:04,328
Honey.

488
00:38:04,412 --> 00:38:05,538
We don't know for sure.

489
00:38:05,621 --> 00:38:07,832
Beom-seok wouldn't do that.

490
00:38:07,915 --> 00:38:09,542
Find out if he's still in Korea.

491
00:38:10,251 --> 00:38:11,335
Yes, sir.

492
00:38:11,419 --> 00:38:12,420
Pack up.

493
00:38:13,713 --> 00:38:15,214
-Already?
-The day is ruined.

494
00:38:15,298 --> 00:38:16,382
Let's go home.

495
00:38:17,717 --> 00:38:20,011
-Honey, do you remember that boy?
-What?

496
00:38:20,928 --> 00:38:24,598
It happened over two decades ago.

497
00:38:24,682 --> 00:38:27,143
That incident where
the German Shepherd of a brewery died,

498
00:38:27,226 --> 00:38:29,061
and the killer
turned out to be a little boy.

499
00:38:29,145 --> 00:38:31,939
Right, the one
from the Evergreen Hope Orphanage.

500
00:38:32,023 --> 00:38:35,818
He received a scholarship
from Queens Group because he was so smart.

501
00:38:35,901 --> 00:38:38,362
I fed him several times when he visited.

502
00:38:38,446 --> 00:38:39,447
Yes, him.

503
00:38:39,530 --> 00:38:42,366
Remember what he said to the police?

504
00:38:42,450 --> 00:38:43,993
This is you, isn't it?

505
00:38:46,412 --> 00:38:48,789
Why would you kill someone's precious dog?

506
00:38:48,873 --> 00:38:50,499
I won't let this pass.

507
00:38:50,583 --> 00:38:52,418
Do you know how much he cost?

508
00:38:53,252 --> 00:38:54,253
I'm sorry.

509
00:38:54,795 --> 00:38:56,589
Apologize to him this instant.

510
00:38:58,507 --> 00:39:01,177
What makes a precious dog any different?

511
00:39:04,180 --> 00:39:05,890
Then would it be okay to kill

512
00:39:07,683 --> 00:39:09,143
a normal dog?

513
00:39:10,102 --> 00:39:12,021
What's wrong with that kid?

514
00:39:12,104 --> 00:39:13,147
Gosh, what is he saying?

515
00:39:14,482 --> 00:39:15,691
Gosh, you're right.

516
00:39:15,775 --> 00:39:17,109
He did ask that question.

517
00:39:17,902 --> 00:39:20,196
It was creepy to hear a boy say that.

518
00:39:20,279 --> 00:39:22,031
-Didn't he look like him?
-Who?

519
00:40:07,368 --> 00:40:09,286
Hey, it's me. Did you get home safe?

520
00:40:10,037 --> 00:40:11,831
I booked you a meeting with Mr. Hermann.

521
00:40:12,957 --> 00:40:13,999
Are you serious?

522
00:40:15,418 --> 00:40:16,502
Thanks.

523
00:40:16,585 --> 00:40:17,878
Okay, see you then.

524
00:40:18,629 --> 00:40:19,839
You won't be disappointed.

525
00:40:31,517 --> 00:40:32,351
ALL MAIL

526
00:40:49,326 --> 00:40:50,536
WE APOLOGIZE…

527
00:40:55,374 --> 00:40:56,417
I'm going

528
00:40:58,127 --> 00:40:59,128
to die?

529
00:40:59,211 --> 00:41:01,130
When Hercyna is just around the corner?

530
00:41:01,714 --> 00:41:03,632
When I'm this close
to the One Trillion Club?

531
00:41:07,344 --> 00:41:08,471
Impossible.

532
00:41:09,388 --> 00:41:11,765
I have so many limited editions
that I haven't worn yet.

533
00:41:11,849 --> 00:41:14,643
I bought so many islands
but haven't visited them yet.

534
00:41:16,187 --> 00:41:17,980
And yet, I'm going to die?

535
00:41:18,063 --> 00:41:19,982
No, that'd be such a waste.

536
00:41:26,113 --> 00:41:27,865
I bought all these from artists

537
00:41:27,948 --> 00:41:30,367
in their nineties
because posthumous works skyrocket.

538
00:41:30,451 --> 00:41:34,163
So how could I die before them?

539
00:41:38,792 --> 00:41:39,877
That'd be such a waste.

540
00:41:57,937 --> 00:41:59,438
You'd be the biggest waste.

541
00:42:05,402 --> 00:42:08,239
Then let's wrap up this store's contract.

542
00:42:08,322 --> 00:42:09,823
Good work, everyone.

543
00:43:18,309 --> 00:43:19,810
-Secretary Na.
-Yes, ma'am?

544
00:43:19,893 --> 00:43:23,522
Are there women whose hearts still race
when they see their husbands

545
00:43:23,606 --> 00:43:25,733
despite being married
for over three years?

546
00:43:25,816 --> 00:43:27,359
Why would their hearts race?

547
00:43:27,985 --> 00:43:30,279
-Do they have arrhythmia?
-No, not that.

548
00:43:30,362 --> 00:43:31,363
Maybe…

549
00:43:32,031 --> 00:43:33,032
because…

550
00:43:33,824 --> 00:43:34,658
they're handsome?

551
00:43:35,492 --> 00:43:37,244
-Their husbands?
-Yes.

552
00:43:37,828 --> 00:43:39,496
Maybe she's ill.

553
00:43:41,665 --> 00:43:43,000
Do you know someone like that?

554
00:43:43,083 --> 00:43:45,294
Yes, I do.

555
00:43:47,379 --> 00:43:50,924
On some days,
she looks him in the eye

556
00:43:52,551 --> 00:43:54,094
and wants to embrace him.

557
00:43:54,595 --> 00:43:55,763
Why?

558
00:43:56,680 --> 00:43:58,891
Because she pities him.

559
00:43:59,808 --> 00:44:01,769
She feels bad

560
00:44:01,852 --> 00:44:05,773
that such a soft soul
has to endure this harsh world.

561
00:44:06,607 --> 00:44:08,692
-No way.
-On other days,

562
00:44:08,776 --> 00:44:10,819
his shoulders look

563
00:44:10,903 --> 00:44:11,945
so broad.

564
00:44:12,738 --> 00:44:15,366
She wants him to hold her.

565
00:44:15,449 --> 00:44:18,410
He looks like a walking, sexy dynamite.

566
00:44:18,494 --> 00:44:21,288
She wonders
if she should let the homme fatal

567
00:44:21,372 --> 00:44:24,291
roam freely in this world.

568
00:44:25,459 --> 00:44:29,922
Please tell her
to see a doctor. She's ill.

569
00:44:30,714 --> 00:44:32,424
-Do you think so?
-I'm telling you.

570
00:44:32,508 --> 00:44:35,386
Make sure she gets a brain CT scan.

571
00:44:35,469 --> 00:44:37,221
Something's seriously wrong up there.

572
00:44:38,347 --> 00:44:39,348
Secretary Na.

573
00:44:40,724 --> 00:44:41,767
You're pretty good.

574
00:44:42,976 --> 00:44:45,688
-I've been very strange these days.
-How so?

575
00:44:45,771 --> 00:44:47,314
I feel sympathy

576
00:44:48,107 --> 00:44:49,316
for others.

577
00:44:50,150 --> 00:44:52,361
-Is that strange?
-I was never like this.

578
00:44:53,237 --> 00:44:54,905
I've always been cold-hearted.

579
00:44:56,115 --> 00:44:57,116
So it's odd.

580
00:45:01,912 --> 00:45:02,913
You're so noisy.

581
00:45:03,414 --> 00:45:05,916
Stop crying
when I'm sacrificing my arm for you.

582
00:45:06,542 --> 00:45:08,752
And I keep empathizing

583
00:45:09,503 --> 00:45:10,504
with others.

584
00:45:24,768 --> 00:45:25,644
What was that?

585
00:45:25,728 --> 00:45:27,479
Solicitors aren't allowed here.

586
00:45:27,563 --> 00:45:29,898
I'm sorry. He's my acquaintance's husband.

587
00:45:30,691 --> 00:45:32,484
So you're doing him a favor?

588
00:45:32,568 --> 00:45:34,194
Their baby is in an incubator.

589
00:45:34,278 --> 00:45:35,487
I felt bad so…

590
00:45:36,363 --> 00:45:37,281
He won't come back.

591
00:45:37,364 --> 00:45:39,491
-I'm sorry.
-How long does the baby…

592
00:45:39,575 --> 00:45:40,826
Sorry?

593
00:45:40,909 --> 00:45:42,035
…have to be in there?

594
00:45:42,953 --> 00:45:45,289
-About three-
-Forget it. One week? Two?

595
00:45:45,372 --> 00:45:48,959
I'll only let him come by until then.

596
00:45:49,042 --> 00:45:50,127
You'll let him do that?

597
00:45:50,210 --> 00:45:53,922
I better not see him
once his baby is discharged.

598
00:45:54,923 --> 00:45:57,134
No insurance will cover it.

599
00:45:57,217 --> 00:45:59,511
I wanted to use
our security deposit for her surgery,

600
00:45:59,595 --> 00:46:00,888
but my mom won't listen.

601
00:46:00,971 --> 00:46:03,432
She says it's my wedding money.

602
00:46:05,017 --> 00:46:06,226
Money is always the problem.

603
00:46:07,478 --> 00:46:08,562
I'm sorry.

604
00:46:19,072 --> 00:46:20,073
Unbelievable.

605
00:46:22,367 --> 00:46:24,369
Her mom isn't the only one who's sick.

606
00:46:25,579 --> 00:46:28,040
Her mom can get treated,
so why would she cry…

607
00:46:34,713 --> 00:46:37,424
Why are there so many sick people?

608
00:46:39,635 --> 00:46:40,761
How annoying.

609
00:46:41,345 --> 00:46:42,471
I was never like this.

610
00:46:43,013 --> 00:46:44,973
I never cared

611
00:46:45,057 --> 00:46:47,392
about people's pain,
so why am I like this?

612
00:46:49,144 --> 00:46:50,979
My husband makes my heart race.

613
00:46:52,397 --> 00:46:56,568
I believe my brain
isn't functioning properly.

614
00:46:56,652 --> 00:46:58,529
Are these symptoms of my illness?

615
00:46:58,612 --> 00:47:00,155
Not really.

616
00:47:00,239 --> 00:47:04,993
Many terminally ill patients
experience such changes of heart.

617
00:47:06,036 --> 00:47:08,205
They realize things
that they wouldn't have realized

618
00:47:08,288 --> 00:47:09,498
if they weren't dying.

619
00:47:09,581 --> 00:47:11,250
"You're changing because of death."

620
00:47:12,543 --> 00:47:13,919
"You're going to die soon."

621
00:47:14,002 --> 00:47:16,338
I think that's what you're insinuating.

622
00:47:16,421 --> 00:47:17,840
But you're wrong.

623
00:47:17,923 --> 00:47:20,926
You see, I've been
on the brink of death many times.

624
00:47:21,009 --> 00:47:22,302
And my miraculous luck

625
00:47:23,303 --> 00:47:24,930
saved me every time.

626
00:47:32,312 --> 00:47:34,940
If you're not skilled enough to save me,

627
00:47:35,023 --> 00:47:36,525
then just watch.

628
00:47:37,734 --> 00:47:38,944
Another miracle

629
00:47:40,070 --> 00:47:41,196
will save me.

630
00:47:47,286 --> 00:47:48,579
Hey, Hyun-woo.

631
00:47:52,833 --> 00:47:53,750
Long time no see.

632
00:47:55,252 --> 00:47:58,088
Yes, I went to the hunting ground!
So what?

633
00:47:58,171 --> 00:47:59,047
Why did you?

634
00:47:59,131 --> 00:48:02,092
To see Father.
He's there around this time of the year.

635
00:48:02,175 --> 00:48:04,177
But you left without seeing him.

636
00:48:04,261 --> 00:48:05,470
Are you

637
00:48:05,554 --> 00:48:06,513
suspecting me?

638
00:48:06,597 --> 00:48:10,058
The fence was pried open
and there was bait nearby.

639
00:48:10,142 --> 00:48:13,437
Then the boar that had been shot
attacked Hae-in.

640
00:48:14,646 --> 00:48:16,106
-Someone purposely--
-So?

641
00:48:19,693 --> 00:48:21,236
My daughter almost died.

642
00:48:22,446 --> 00:48:23,739
Tell me the truth.

643
00:48:23,822 --> 00:48:25,532
This is your last warning.

644
00:48:28,076 --> 00:48:29,912
You're upset because Hae-in was involved.

645
00:48:30,662 --> 00:48:33,415
Why weren't you upset
when I was falsely accused and kicked out?

646
00:48:37,336 --> 00:48:38,337
Fine, sit down.

647
00:48:41,089 --> 00:48:44,968
I went there because I knew
it was the family's hunting day.

648
00:48:45,928 --> 00:48:48,347
But when I went there,
the great Moh Seul-hee said

649
00:48:48,430 --> 00:48:50,557
he was asleep and didn't let me see him.

650
00:48:50,641 --> 00:48:52,434
I begged her but to no avail.

651
00:48:53,143 --> 00:48:54,728
So I came back. That's all.

652
00:48:56,480 --> 00:48:57,356
Fine.

653
00:48:58,106 --> 00:48:59,107
Beom-jun.

654
00:48:59,775 --> 00:49:01,777
Help me meet him just once.

655
00:49:03,403 --> 00:49:06,323
That's all I need.
I want to reconcile before it's too late.

656
00:49:07,115 --> 00:49:08,241
Sometimes,

657
00:49:09,618 --> 00:49:12,162
it's better to let go.

658
00:49:29,805 --> 00:49:30,931
Hyun-woo.

659
00:49:31,765 --> 00:49:33,016
Isn't my family so odd?

660
00:49:33,642 --> 00:49:35,644
Sorry? Not at all, sir.

661
00:49:35,727 --> 00:49:38,397
We have seven lawsuits against each other.

662
00:49:38,480 --> 00:49:42,484
You must've walked
on eggshells as you took care

663
00:49:42,567 --> 00:49:44,403
of our trivial matters.

664
00:49:48,323 --> 00:49:49,157
You've done so much.

665
00:50:00,877 --> 00:50:01,878
Hello.

666
00:50:05,007 --> 00:50:06,425
The chairman is already asleep.

667
00:50:07,259 --> 00:50:08,218
Already?

668
00:50:08,885 --> 00:50:10,345
Should I wake him up?

669
00:50:10,429 --> 00:50:11,471
That's okay.

670
00:50:11,555 --> 00:50:13,515
I just came by to greet him.

671
00:50:13,598 --> 00:50:14,433
Goodbye then.

672
00:50:19,604 --> 00:50:20,647
Ms. Moh.

673
00:50:21,857 --> 00:50:24,568
Did Beom-seok come to our hunting ground

674
00:50:25,861 --> 00:50:27,070
and ask to see Father?

675
00:50:28,321 --> 00:50:30,699
No, he didn't.

676
00:50:31,992 --> 00:50:33,160
Is that what he said?

677
00:50:36,621 --> 00:50:37,622
Look.

678
00:50:38,498 --> 00:50:40,083
I don't like saying this,

679
00:50:41,168 --> 00:50:42,502
but be wary of him.

680
00:50:42,586 --> 00:50:46,214
He's been holding a grudge for a while
after getting kicked out.

681
00:50:46,298 --> 00:50:48,967
Those who have nothing to lose
are the most fearful.

682
00:50:59,144 --> 00:51:02,230
What kind of person
is Mr. Yoon Eun-sung? Do you know?

683
00:51:02,314 --> 00:51:03,440
Mr. Yoon?

684
00:51:03,523 --> 00:51:07,402
I know his business side,
but not him as a person.

685
00:51:07,903 --> 00:51:12,574
You know that people like us
shouldn't trust others easily.

686
00:51:12,657 --> 00:51:15,535
If this deal
goes down the drain as well,

687
00:51:15,619 --> 00:51:17,329
Father will abandon Soo-cheol.

688
00:51:17,412 --> 00:51:18,413
Don't worry.

689
00:51:18,497 --> 00:51:20,707
I'll look into him discreetly.

690
00:51:58,036 --> 00:51:59,162
Looking for me?

691
00:51:59,246 --> 00:52:02,082
Gosh, you startled me.

692
00:52:08,713 --> 00:52:09,840
A background check?

693
00:52:10,841 --> 00:52:12,217
She's quite cautious.

694
00:52:12,300 --> 00:52:14,594
She's just afraid,

695
00:52:14,678 --> 00:52:17,013
but it's only in the beginning.

696
00:52:17,097 --> 00:52:20,267
People like her trust easily
once they let down their guard.

697
00:52:21,351 --> 00:52:22,811
She did let down her guard somewhat.

698
00:52:23,687 --> 00:52:27,357
By the way, do you see
any hope with Hae-in?

699
00:52:29,442 --> 00:52:32,028
Money is important to me for sure,

700
00:52:32,112 --> 00:52:34,656
but I'd also love to see
that couple break up.

701
00:52:35,448 --> 00:52:36,324
Why?

702
00:52:36,408 --> 00:52:41,788
It's safe to say that I pioneered
the matchmaking scene in this country.

703
00:52:41,872 --> 00:52:44,624
Yet I failed
to properly marry off Queens' daughter.

704
00:52:44,708 --> 00:52:46,418
How humiliating is that?

705
00:52:46,501 --> 00:52:48,712
I will tear them apart at all costs

706
00:52:48,795 --> 00:52:51,047
and retrieve my lost honor
and performance.

707
00:52:52,716 --> 00:52:55,510
In that case,
don't repeat what you did.

708
00:52:56,511 --> 00:52:58,180
-You'll get in the way.
-That was…

709
00:52:58,722 --> 00:53:01,141
I was told to do that.

710
00:53:02,267 --> 00:53:06,104
But Hyun-woo stepped in, killed the boar,

711
00:53:06,188 --> 00:53:07,189
and saved Hae-in.

712
00:53:07,272 --> 00:53:09,900
I never saw that coming.

713
00:53:11,818 --> 00:53:14,112
Hyun-woo, you've leveled up.

714
00:53:14,779 --> 00:53:18,074
From Mr. Cinderella
who married into a wealthy family

715
00:53:18,158 --> 00:53:20,619
to a lifesaver
who saved their daughter's life!

716
00:53:21,995 --> 00:53:23,914
They are treating me differently now.

717
00:53:23,997 --> 00:53:26,416
It was my first time eating
a pheasant leg.

718
00:53:26,499 --> 00:53:29,169
I was normally given
the neck or the lean cuts.

719
00:53:29,252 --> 00:53:31,254
But my father-in-law gave me the leg.

720
00:53:32,422 --> 00:53:34,966
It's too early to be complacent.

721
00:53:35,050 --> 00:53:36,676
Keep up the good work.

722
00:53:38,386 --> 00:53:39,387
How?

723
00:53:39,471 --> 00:53:43,350
"I was only doing my job."

724
00:53:43,433 --> 00:53:47,354
Don't ruin this opportunity
by saying such nonsense.

725
00:53:47,437 --> 00:53:52,067
"Yes, I was scared too. I could've died,
but I did it for Hae-in."

726
00:53:53,026 --> 00:53:54,819
You need to take credit.

727
00:53:56,655 --> 00:53:58,114
-Do I have to?
-Yes, you do.

728
00:53:58,198 --> 00:54:00,992
Taking credit
is like collecting coffee coupons.

729
00:54:01,076 --> 00:54:03,370
You need to collect ten coupons

730
00:54:03,453 --> 00:54:06,748
for them to realize
you're a regular and give you freebies.

731
00:54:07,457 --> 00:54:08,458
I don't need

732
00:54:09,334 --> 00:54:10,335
any freebies.

733
00:54:10,418 --> 00:54:13,213
All I want is to be free and unscathed.

734
00:54:13,296 --> 00:54:15,090
What an idiot.

735
00:54:15,173 --> 00:54:16,675
Say goodbye if you're going

736
00:54:16,758 --> 00:54:17,926
-to be fake.
-Goodbye to what?

737
00:54:18,009 --> 00:54:19,886
"Goodbye, my Italian suits."

738
00:54:19,970 --> 00:54:21,763
"Goodbye, my handmade designer shoes."

739
00:54:21,846 --> 00:54:24,015
"Goodbye, my foreign car."

740
00:54:24,099 --> 00:54:27,435
"Goodbye, the luxury watch on my wrist."

741
00:54:27,519 --> 00:54:30,772
"Goodbye, Hae-in's fortune."

742
00:54:32,148 --> 00:54:35,944
Mr. Cinderella will now return
to his orchard down south.

743
00:54:36,027 --> 00:54:40,490
But the problem is, his family
won't welcome him with open arms.

744
00:54:43,159 --> 00:54:44,911
I'm sorry, Coach.

745
00:54:44,995 --> 00:54:48,498
My son isn't interested in boxing
and wants to do Taekwondo instead.

746
00:54:48,581 --> 00:54:50,667
That's okay. Kids are like that.

747
00:54:51,543 --> 00:54:52,669
Goodbye then.

748
00:54:52,752 --> 00:54:53,837
Let's go.

749
00:54:53,920 --> 00:54:56,172
By the way, Jae-hyeon,
why do you like Taekwondo?

750
00:54:56,256 --> 00:54:58,550
They have belts.

751
00:54:58,633 --> 00:55:00,093
Belts? For your waist?

752
00:55:00,176 --> 00:55:01,553
Is that why?

753
00:55:02,929 --> 00:55:04,889
That's why he wants to go.

754
00:55:05,473 --> 00:55:08,101
Jae-hyeon, we have belts too.

755
00:55:08,184 --> 00:55:09,227
Look at that.

756
00:55:09,311 --> 00:55:10,520
It's the champion belt.

757
00:55:10,603 --> 00:55:12,856
Coach, that's okay.

758
00:55:15,191 --> 00:55:16,359
-Ta-da.
-Gosh.

759
00:55:16,443 --> 00:55:17,444
Check this out.

760
00:55:17,527 --> 00:55:20,739
What do you say?
Isn't it fancier than those belts?

761
00:55:20,822 --> 00:55:22,282
They smash things too.

762
00:55:23,116 --> 00:55:24,117
Smash?

763
00:55:24,576 --> 00:55:26,828
We smash things too.

764
00:55:26,911 --> 00:55:29,581
We just didn't have time.
Should I show you?

765
00:55:29,664 --> 00:55:31,207
No, you don't need to show him.

766
00:55:31,291 --> 00:55:32,208
Hold on.

767
00:55:32,292 --> 00:55:33,585
Give me one second.

768
00:55:33,668 --> 00:55:34,878
Where's the board?

769
00:55:34,961 --> 00:55:35,962
There it is.

770
00:55:36,880 --> 00:55:37,881
Okay. Look.

771
00:55:37,964 --> 00:55:39,507
Check this out.

772
00:55:48,016 --> 00:55:49,517
This is how you do it.

773
00:55:49,601 --> 00:55:51,227
I'll smash it this time around.

774
00:55:51,311 --> 00:55:52,312
Watch me.

775
00:56:02,697 --> 00:56:04,282
Gosh!

776
00:56:04,366 --> 00:56:06,368
See? I smashed it, right?

777
00:56:06,451 --> 00:56:08,912
-Isn't boxing cool too?
-But…

778
00:56:09,829 --> 00:56:11,414
What? What is it this time?

779
00:56:11,498 --> 00:56:14,084
I want to do Taekwondo
because Ji-seong does it.

780
00:56:14,167 --> 00:56:17,545
Ji-seong is his best friend.

781
00:56:17,629 --> 00:56:18,671
I see.

782
00:56:19,589 --> 00:56:20,799
Ma'am.

783
00:56:20,882 --> 00:56:24,719
I'm only saying this
because I care a lot about Jae-hyeon.

784
00:56:24,803 --> 00:56:28,014
Don't you think
he should have various friends?

785
00:56:28,098 --> 00:56:28,973
Sorry?

786
00:56:29,057 --> 00:56:30,975
-Do you know Baek Ho-yeol?
-I do.

787
00:56:31,851 --> 00:56:35,313
He's my son, and he's just like you.

788
00:56:35,397 --> 00:56:37,440
He loves games just like you.

789
00:56:37,524 --> 00:56:40,276
How great would it be to come here to box

790
00:56:40,360 --> 00:56:42,695
and play games with him after school?

791
00:56:46,241 --> 00:56:47,742
Ho-yeol has the lowest grade.

792
00:56:47,826 --> 00:56:48,827
Hey.

793
00:56:52,122 --> 00:56:53,665
Coach.

794
00:56:53,748 --> 00:56:54,791
You're bleeding.

795
00:56:57,127 --> 00:56:58,169
Gosh.

796
00:56:58,753 --> 00:56:59,712
Why am I…

797
00:57:00,380 --> 00:57:02,340
Gosh, don't worry about me.

798
00:57:02,424 --> 00:57:04,175
The wood must've scraped me.

799
00:57:04,259 --> 00:57:05,718
Goodbye then.

800
00:57:05,802 --> 00:57:06,803
Are you leaving?

801
00:57:06,886 --> 00:57:08,888
-Let's go.
-Get home safe, ma'am.

802
00:57:08,972 --> 00:57:10,306
Goodbye.

803
00:57:10,390 --> 00:57:11,516
Okay.

804
00:57:11,599 --> 00:57:13,726
Jae-hyeon, see you again!

805
00:57:14,269 --> 00:57:15,270
Bye.

806
00:57:15,353 --> 00:57:16,521
Goodbye, ma'am.

807
00:57:33,872 --> 00:57:35,748
-Hey, you're bleeding.
-It's just a scrape.

808
00:57:35,832 --> 00:57:37,125
The wood scraped me.

809
00:57:37,208 --> 00:57:39,002
Why are you so irritated?

810
00:57:39,085 --> 00:57:42,797
I haven't been getting much sleep lately,
so I closed down my salon today.

811
00:57:42,881 --> 00:57:44,632
I should close down this gym soon

812
00:57:44,716 --> 00:57:47,177
and consider working under someone
once Hyun-woo divorces.

813
00:57:47,260 --> 00:57:48,887
Stop talking about his divorce.

814
00:57:48,970 --> 00:57:51,931
I should accept reality
and prepare myself.

815
00:57:55,018 --> 00:57:56,936
-Should we go to Seoul?
-And do what?

816
00:57:57,020 --> 00:57:59,230
I called Hae-in, but she didn't pick up.

817
00:57:59,314 --> 00:58:02,692
Let's meet her in person and dissuade her
from getting a divorce.

818
00:58:03,193 --> 00:58:04,569
-Get ready.
-What?

819
00:58:04,652 --> 00:58:05,904
Let's go.

820
00:58:05,987 --> 00:58:12,327
You were so against this whole plan,
but I guess you eventually got into it.

821
00:58:13,077 --> 00:58:14,078
Well…

822
00:58:14,162 --> 00:58:17,499
I always do my best
when I set my mind to something.

823
00:58:17,582 --> 00:58:18,583
You're right.

824
00:58:18,666 --> 00:58:20,502
You always do things wholeheartedly.

825
00:58:20,585 --> 00:58:22,045
But here's the problem.

826
00:58:22,128 --> 00:58:24,839
Fool her halfheartedly,
and all will be fine.

827
00:58:24,923 --> 00:58:26,549
But do an outstanding job,

828
00:58:27,800 --> 00:58:30,929
and she'll be livid
if she finds out.

829
00:58:33,431 --> 00:58:34,682
-Probably, right?
-Right.

830
00:58:34,766 --> 00:58:38,770
So you should never get caught. Got that?

831
00:58:39,812 --> 00:58:41,439
I won't get caught

832
00:58:42,148 --> 00:58:43,525
as long as you and I

833
00:58:44,150 --> 00:58:45,443
keep this a secret.

834
00:58:45,527 --> 00:58:46,486
Right.

835
00:58:49,364 --> 00:58:53,826
By the way, shouldn't we tell Hyun-woo
that we're going to see Hae-in?

836
00:58:54,661 --> 00:58:55,662
You idiot.

837
00:58:55,745 --> 00:58:58,414
Do you think he'll allow that?
We've got nothing to lose now.

838
00:58:58,498 --> 00:59:00,959
We should try to stop them
at all costs, right?

839
00:59:02,460 --> 00:59:03,586
Step on it.

840
00:59:11,052 --> 00:59:13,179
ONGOING RECRUITMENT

841
00:59:27,443 --> 00:59:28,945
What should we tell them?

842
00:59:29,904 --> 00:59:32,198
We don't need to introduce ourselves.

843
00:59:32,282 --> 00:59:33,658
Do you not watch dramas?

844
00:59:34,158 --> 00:59:37,120
The secretary's office manages
the VIP families.

845
00:59:37,203 --> 00:59:40,707
They'll be startled the moment
they see our faces and say,

846
00:59:40,790 --> 00:59:42,959
"Ms. Hong, your sister-in-law is here."

847
00:59:43,042 --> 00:59:45,878
Then they'll let us in right away.

848
00:59:45,962 --> 00:59:47,755
You need to book an appointment.

849
00:59:49,424 --> 00:59:51,009
You must be new here.

850
01:00:03,021 --> 01:00:04,147
Look at this.

851
01:00:04,230 --> 01:00:05,523
That's me.

852
01:00:05,607 --> 01:00:07,567
This wavy-haired guy is him.

853
01:00:08,151 --> 01:00:11,195
Okay? That's us. See?

854
01:00:12,655 --> 01:00:15,533
Leave your name and number,
and I'll hand it to her.

855
01:00:16,743 --> 01:00:17,744
Look.

856
01:00:18,661 --> 01:00:21,664
We're her family.
We're part of the royal family.

857
01:00:21,748 --> 01:00:24,042
Why must we book
an appointment to see our family?

858
01:00:24,709 --> 01:00:25,918
Jeez.

859
01:00:26,002 --> 01:00:29,589
Please book an appointment and come back--

860
01:00:33,926 --> 01:00:34,969
Hae-in!

861
01:00:35,053 --> 01:00:36,888
Long time no see.

862
01:00:36,971 --> 01:00:38,473
I'm Hyeon-tae, Hyun-woo's brother.

863
01:00:39,766 --> 01:00:40,933
I know.

864
01:00:41,517 --> 01:00:44,020
I wondered if it was you, and I was right.

865
01:00:44,103 --> 01:00:47,815
We need to talk. Even Hyun-woo
doesn't know that we're here.

866
01:00:48,858 --> 01:00:49,859
Well…

867
01:00:53,279 --> 01:00:54,781
Should we go upstairs?

868
01:00:54,864 --> 01:00:55,740
All right.

869
01:00:57,450 --> 01:00:58,576
-This way.
-Okay.

870
01:01:05,958 --> 01:01:07,168
Are you surprised?

871
01:01:07,251 --> 01:01:11,255
But you see, we won't punish you
for not recognizing us.

872
01:01:11,798 --> 01:01:12,799
Don't worry.

873
01:01:12,882 --> 01:01:17,220
We don't abuse our power in that manner.

874
01:01:27,772 --> 01:01:28,856
You must be busy.

875
01:01:28,940 --> 01:01:31,317
Sorry we came by unannounced.

876
01:01:31,401 --> 01:01:35,071
I had actually called several times,
but I couldn't reach you.

877
01:01:35,154 --> 01:01:36,781
I don't pick up unsaved numbers.

878
01:01:37,907 --> 01:01:40,118
You must not have my number.

879
01:01:41,369 --> 01:01:42,745
What brings you here?

880
01:01:42,829 --> 01:01:43,996
You see…

881
01:01:46,207 --> 01:01:48,501
Where should I begin?

882
01:01:50,545 --> 01:01:53,256
It was our dad's 60th birthday recently.

883
01:01:53,881 --> 01:01:57,427
You must be here because you were upset
that I didn't show up.

884
01:01:57,510 --> 01:01:58,386
Gosh, not at all.
No?

885
01:01:59,387 --> 01:02:02,515
Of course not,
because we weren't upset at all.

886
01:02:06,018 --> 01:02:08,187
I don't know how you'll feel about this,

887
01:02:09,021 --> 01:02:10,356
but Hyun-woo…

888
01:02:10,440 --> 01:02:12,150
-Yes?
-He's difficult, isn't he?

889
01:02:12,775 --> 01:02:14,986
-Sorry?
-Gosh, I understand.

890
01:02:15,069 --> 01:02:16,070
Understand what?

891
01:02:16,154 --> 01:02:19,949
The person who's the polar opposite of you
isn't on the other side of the globe.

892
01:02:20,032 --> 01:02:25,121
It's the person you're married to,
the one you sleep and eat next to.

893
01:02:25,204 --> 01:02:28,124
They fail to understand you the most.

894
01:02:28,207 --> 01:02:29,083
Right.

895
01:02:29,167 --> 01:02:31,878
My husband and I
argued all the time because of the AC.

896
01:02:31,961 --> 01:02:34,672
He'd turn on the AC in the summer,
and I'd be freezing.

897
01:02:34,756 --> 01:02:37,216
We even cursed each other out
because of it.

898
01:02:40,845 --> 01:02:43,681
He used to be head over heels
for me when we got married,

899
01:02:43,765 --> 01:02:45,892
yet he couldn't even
turn off the AC for me.

900
01:02:45,975 --> 01:02:48,895
We don't argue over such things.

901
01:02:48,978 --> 01:02:50,730
Is that so?

902
01:02:50,813 --> 01:02:52,106
Then that's great.

903
01:02:52,190 --> 01:02:53,649
You have a good relationship.

904
01:02:53,733 --> 01:02:56,110
We sleep in separate rooms,
so we each have an AC.

905
01:02:58,404 --> 01:03:01,783
That's understandable
if you have many spare rooms.

906
01:03:01,866 --> 01:03:05,077
Anyway, this is what
I say to him all the time.

907
01:03:05,161 --> 01:03:07,330
"Now that you're married,
you're no longer one of us.

908
01:03:07,413 --> 01:03:10,958
Consider yourself a part of Queens
and stay there even after you die."

909
01:03:11,042 --> 01:03:14,128
"Don't you dare come back
or set foot into our house."

910
01:03:15,963 --> 01:03:17,381
So speaking of which…

911
01:03:26,682 --> 01:03:27,892
Div--

912
01:03:29,727 --> 01:03:32,271
I'm sorry to interrupt,
but you're going to be late

913
01:03:32,355 --> 01:03:34,398
for your meeting with Mr. Hermann.

914
01:03:34,482 --> 01:03:36,192
I'm sorry, but I need to go.

915
01:03:36,275 --> 01:03:37,944
I have an important dinner today.

916
01:03:38,027 --> 01:03:39,654
Okay, you should go.

917
01:03:39,737 --> 01:03:42,365
I'll text you
the rest of the conversation,

918
01:03:42,448 --> 01:03:44,116
so please save my number.

919
01:03:52,583 --> 01:03:55,628
-I'll visit you sometime soon.
-Really? Would you do that?

920
01:03:55,711 --> 01:04:00,049
I admit that we've been distant
after Hyun-woo got married.

921
01:04:00,132 --> 01:04:02,468
After all, you got us a building.

922
01:04:02,552 --> 01:04:03,469
A building?

923
01:04:03,553 --> 01:04:05,555
Yes, the one in our town.

924
01:04:05,638 --> 01:04:08,182
Did I purchase a building there?

925
01:04:08,266 --> 01:04:11,143
Yes, you did. You told me
to get one when you got married.

926
01:04:12,103 --> 01:04:13,187
I see.

927
01:04:14,105 --> 01:04:15,106
Are you using that?

928
01:04:15,189 --> 01:04:16,399
Yes.

929
01:04:17,233 --> 01:04:18,568
But don't you worry.

930
01:04:18,651 --> 01:04:20,653
I do the cleaning and repairing.

931
01:04:20,736 --> 01:04:21,863
I do everything.

932
01:04:21,946 --> 01:04:24,991
Don't you worry about the building
since I have it under control.

933
01:04:29,412 --> 01:04:32,373
By the way, why did your in-laws visit?

934
01:04:32,456 --> 01:04:33,541
I'm not sure.

935
01:04:34,166 --> 01:04:36,377
She mentioned
how I didn't attend her father's 60th.

936
01:04:36,878 --> 01:04:38,504
So she came to nitpick?

937
01:04:38,588 --> 01:04:39,630
She said no.

938
01:04:39,714 --> 01:04:40,548
Then?

939
01:04:42,383 --> 01:04:46,679
She said marriage
was like turning the AC on in the summer.

940
01:04:47,388 --> 01:04:49,515
What? What does that mean?

941
01:04:50,141 --> 01:04:51,642
You never agree on the temperature.

942
01:04:52,435 --> 01:04:53,603
I see.

943
01:04:53,686 --> 01:04:55,313
That makes sense.

944
01:05:07,241 --> 01:05:08,117
Hey.

945
01:05:08,951 --> 01:05:10,703
-Where's Mr. Hermann?
-Right.

946
01:05:10,786 --> 01:05:13,581
He went to see his baby daughter
because she flipped over.

947
01:05:14,165 --> 01:05:17,710
He ditched this meeting
just because his baby flipped over?

948
01:05:17,793 --> 01:05:19,003
He's a family guy.

949
01:05:19,086 --> 01:05:22,298
That must be why he divorced four times
and had a baby at 60.

950
01:05:22,381 --> 01:05:23,549
How irritating.

951
01:05:24,216 --> 01:05:27,136
I even brought the floor plan
since he wanted to see it first.

952
01:05:27,219 --> 01:05:28,971
This is actually better.

953
01:05:29,055 --> 01:05:31,933
You see, he already has a picture in mind.

954
01:05:32,642 --> 01:05:35,019
Knowing that beforehand
would give you an advantage.

955
01:05:35,645 --> 01:05:36,812
What does he want?

956
01:05:39,315 --> 01:05:41,108
What? You're back?

957
01:05:41,192 --> 01:05:42,985
I thought you went home.

958
01:05:43,069 --> 01:05:44,612
I have more documents to look over.

959
01:05:44,695 --> 01:05:46,364
-You can go home first.
-Yes, sir.

960
01:05:47,281 --> 01:05:51,160
By the way, Secretary Na told me earlier

961
01:05:51,243 --> 01:05:53,245
that Ms. Hong had a dinner appointment.

962
01:05:53,329 --> 01:05:54,288
I see.

963
01:05:54,872 --> 01:05:57,708
She said Ms. Hong was meeting
with Mr. Yoon Eun-sung

964
01:05:57,792 --> 01:05:59,418
and might come home late. So sir,

965
01:05:59,502 --> 01:06:03,631
I think it's safe for you
to go home instead of staying here.

966
01:06:04,173 --> 01:06:05,466
Who is she meeting again?

967
01:06:07,009 --> 01:06:09,637
Hercyna wants two floors.

968
01:06:09,720 --> 01:06:10,888
-Two floors?
-Yes.

969
01:06:12,014 --> 01:06:14,433
You'll need a fancy staircase around here.

970
01:06:14,517 --> 01:06:16,060
How can we do that?

971
01:06:16,143 --> 01:06:18,020
This won't be a simple renovation.

972
01:06:18,104 --> 01:06:20,731
I'll have to change
the structure and get it approved.

973
01:06:20,815 --> 01:06:24,443
Exactly. He'll make that suggestion
and choose whomever gets it done first.

974
01:06:24,527 --> 01:06:26,320
That's insane.

975
01:06:26,988 --> 01:06:29,365
It's ridiculous…

976
01:06:30,658 --> 01:06:31,659
but only I know this?

977
01:06:31,742 --> 01:06:33,327
Correct.

978
01:06:42,795 --> 01:06:47,091
Sir, did you hear about your siblings
visiting Ms. Hong earlier today?

979
01:06:47,967 --> 01:06:50,720
-Who?
-Your sister and brother.

980
01:06:50,803 --> 01:06:52,972
Secretary Na just told me about it.

981
01:06:53,055 --> 01:06:54,265
Did you not know?

982
01:07:06,027 --> 01:07:07,903
Eat first before they get soggy.

983
01:07:07,987 --> 01:07:11,782
Hold on. "I know it's tough.
Dot, dot, dot."

984
01:07:11,866 --> 01:07:14,201
"But you still can't get a divorce."

985
01:07:14,285 --> 01:07:16,996
"Can you reconsider it for my sake?"

986
01:07:17,079 --> 01:07:19,832
Why would she do that?
She barely knows you.

987
01:07:19,915 --> 01:07:21,584
Just eat your udon.

988
01:07:21,667 --> 01:07:23,794
Why did you mention
cleaning the building to her?

989
01:07:23,878 --> 01:07:25,463
I was so shocked.

990
01:07:25,546 --> 01:07:27,757
How did she not know
about her own building?

991
01:07:27,840 --> 01:07:29,633
Is this similar to how I forgot

992
01:07:29,717 --> 01:07:31,010
about the 10,000 won I left

993
01:07:31,093 --> 01:07:32,428
in my winter coat?

994
01:07:32,511 --> 01:07:33,679
Is that what owning

995
01:07:33,763 --> 01:07:35,848
-a building is to them--
-Stop talking!

996
01:07:40,269 --> 01:07:42,938
"Whatever the reason
for your divorce may be,

997
01:07:43,022 --> 01:07:45,649
I believe Hyun-woo is to blame."

998
01:07:45,733 --> 01:07:49,653
"So could you please
be understanding this once

999
01:07:49,737 --> 01:07:51,989
and not get a divorce? Crying emote."

1000
01:07:55,159 --> 01:07:56,452
I'm sending it.

1001
01:07:59,413 --> 01:08:00,247
It's Hyun-woo!

1002
01:08:00,331 --> 01:08:01,332
BAEK HYUN-WOO

1003
01:08:01,415 --> 01:08:03,793
-What do I do?
-Pick it up.

1004
01:08:06,003 --> 01:08:07,671
What? Yes, I met her.

1005
01:08:07,755 --> 01:08:11,092
Why do you think I did?
To tell her not to divorce you.

1006
01:08:11,175 --> 01:08:13,010
But she was too busy,

1007
01:08:13,094 --> 01:08:14,220
so I texted her instead.

1008
01:08:15,346 --> 01:08:16,889
-What?
-What?

1009
01:08:16,972 --> 01:08:18,390
They're not separating.

1010
01:08:18,474 --> 01:08:20,309
-Did they reconcile?
-Did you reconcile?

1011
01:08:21,602 --> 01:08:24,230
No, she just doesn't know that he wants

1012
01:08:24,313 --> 01:08:25,314
-a divorce.
-What?

1013
01:08:25,397 --> 01:08:26,565
He never brought it up.

1014
01:08:27,525 --> 01:08:28,901
What do I do?

1015
01:08:28,984 --> 01:08:30,069
HONG HAE-IN

1016
01:08:42,248 --> 01:08:43,541
BAEK HYUN-WOO

1017
01:08:45,918 --> 01:08:48,295
POWER OFF

1018
01:08:54,510 --> 01:08:55,511
Are you okay?

1019
01:08:56,011 --> 01:08:57,012
Yes.

1020
01:08:58,681 --> 01:08:59,682
Let's go.

1021
01:09:04,854 --> 01:09:05,855
What kind of person

1022
01:09:06,522 --> 01:09:07,690
is your husband?

1023
01:09:07,773 --> 01:09:08,941
That was random.

1024
01:09:09,024 --> 01:09:11,360
You were always cold
and suspicious of others.

1025
01:09:11,443 --> 01:09:13,737
So I was curious about the person

1026
01:09:14,905 --> 01:09:15,906
you chose to marry.

1027
01:09:17,032 --> 01:09:18,284
Let me think.

1028
01:09:20,035 --> 01:09:22,872
It feels like
you're hoping I'd bad-mouth him.

1029
01:09:22,955 --> 01:09:25,040
But you're wrong. He's a good man.

1030
01:09:25,666 --> 01:09:29,044
You saw how he jumped in
to save me in that dangerous moment.

1031
01:09:31,630 --> 01:09:32,673
You're wrong.

1032
01:09:33,841 --> 01:09:35,509
I saw him hesitating.

1033
01:09:36,218 --> 01:09:37,845
He hesitated

1034
01:09:37,928 --> 01:09:39,513
to save you.

1035
01:09:43,726 --> 01:09:44,727
Hae-in.

1036
01:09:49,148 --> 01:09:50,524
HONG HAE-IN

1037
01:09:51,650 --> 01:09:54,278
The number you have dialed
is not available…

1038
01:10:03,996 --> 01:10:06,123
That's the difference between you two.

1039
01:10:07,249 --> 01:10:10,044
You were watching him at that moment,

1040
01:10:10,794 --> 01:10:11,962
but he was watching me.

1041
01:10:16,884 --> 01:10:18,886
You actually believe that he loves you.

1042
01:10:18,969 --> 01:10:20,179
Yes, I do.

1043
01:10:20,846 --> 01:10:22,973
I don't know what love means to you.

1044
01:10:23,057 --> 01:10:27,645
But to me, it's not about being happy
and whispering sweet nothings.

1045
01:10:27,728 --> 01:10:29,521
Love is when

1046
01:10:29,605 --> 01:10:31,273
you endure the pain together.

1047
01:10:31,357 --> 01:10:33,776
When you choose to stay
instead of running away.

1048
01:10:35,361 --> 01:10:36,654
Even if they have a debt

1049
01:10:37,863 --> 01:10:39,365
or something more than that,

1050
01:10:39,865 --> 01:10:41,158
you still stick together.

1051
01:10:43,410 --> 01:10:44,411
That's love.

1052
01:10:45,496 --> 01:10:46,956
And he's doing just that.

1053
01:10:49,041 --> 01:10:50,042
That was lengthy.

1054
01:10:50,584 --> 01:10:51,460
What?

1055
01:10:51,543 --> 01:10:53,504
People tend to ramble when they're unsure.

1056
01:10:54,546 --> 01:10:56,924
You don't look confident.

1057
01:11:34,503 --> 01:11:35,713
I didn't know you were here.

1058
01:11:35,796 --> 01:11:36,839
Where's Hae-in?

1059
01:11:36,922 --> 01:11:39,216
Well, you see…

1060
01:11:47,975 --> 01:11:49,143
What brings you here?

1061
01:11:49,935 --> 01:11:51,270
Hae-in had a lot to drink.

1062
01:11:52,187 --> 01:11:54,189
She drank?

1063
01:12:00,487 --> 01:12:01,530
Hae-in.

1064
01:12:01,613 --> 01:12:03,907
-Hae-in.
-Let her be. She's sleeping.

1065
01:12:06,076 --> 01:12:08,287
She sleeps when she's drunk.

1066
01:12:13,375 --> 01:12:14,209
Hong Hae-in.

1067
01:12:16,628 --> 01:12:20,007
She's been sleeping the whole time,
so give her ten more minutes.

1068
01:12:20,090 --> 01:12:22,384
Or I'll bring her in later,

1069
01:12:22,468 --> 01:12:23,552
so you can wait inside.

1070
01:12:23,635 --> 01:12:25,471
How much alcohol did you feed her?

1071
01:12:27,806 --> 01:12:28,807
Sorry?

1072
01:12:29,975 --> 01:12:30,976
Look.

1073
01:12:32,353 --> 01:12:35,481
She doesn't usually drink,
but she can hold her liquor.

1074
01:12:35,564 --> 01:12:39,068
So how much did you feed her for her to be

1075
01:12:41,737 --> 01:12:42,988
this drunk?

1076
01:12:43,655 --> 01:12:44,782
I mixed alcohol.

1077
01:12:56,710 --> 01:12:59,755
I can't sleep because you're too noisy.

1078
01:13:02,925 --> 01:13:04,051
Thanks. Go home safely.

1079
01:13:04,968 --> 01:13:06,136
Okay. Sleep well.

1080
01:13:07,137 --> 01:13:09,431
-See you tomorrow evening.
-Why would she--

1081
01:13:11,850 --> 01:13:12,851
I mean…

1082
01:13:13,685 --> 01:13:15,938
I heard you guys met
with Mr. Hermann today.

1083
01:13:16,021 --> 01:13:18,232
So what's tomorrow for?

1084
01:13:18,315 --> 01:13:20,192
Mr. Hermann didn't show up today.

1085
01:13:21,485 --> 01:13:22,486
It was just us two.

1086
01:13:23,112 --> 01:13:24,113
And we drank

1087
01:13:26,031 --> 01:13:26,865
by ourselves.

1088
01:13:32,746 --> 01:13:35,499
Right. Don't forget to drink
orange juice in the morning.

1089
01:13:35,582 --> 01:13:37,167
That's your hangover cure.

1090
01:13:37,251 --> 01:13:39,211
Whatever. Okay.

1091
01:13:39,837 --> 01:13:40,671
Okay.

1092
01:13:40,754 --> 01:13:43,549
-Bye.
-Goodbye then.

1093
01:13:44,216 --> 01:13:46,468
Please take good care of her.

1094
01:13:50,389 --> 01:13:51,515
-Mr. Oh.
-Yes, sir?

1095
01:13:51,598 --> 01:13:54,476
Please take him home safely.
He seems to be very drunk.

1096
01:13:54,560 --> 01:13:57,646
He seems very out of it,
so walk him to his door.

1097
01:13:57,729 --> 01:13:58,730
Yes, sir.

1098
01:13:59,898 --> 01:14:01,859
What are you doing? Get in.

1099
01:14:18,709 --> 01:14:21,211
Why did you suddenly drink so much?

1100
01:14:21,295 --> 01:14:22,880
Because it was unlike me.

1101
01:14:24,047 --> 01:14:26,592
I'm going to try new things from now on.

1102
01:14:30,053 --> 01:14:30,929
It's so unfair.

1103
01:14:31,013 --> 01:14:35,976
I lived differently from others
so I could live a long, healthy life.

1104
01:14:37,644 --> 01:14:39,771
But look at me now. It was all useless.

1105
01:14:41,732 --> 01:14:43,692
I'm going to speak my mind,

1106
01:14:44,318 --> 01:14:47,112
do everything I want,

1107
01:14:50,616 --> 01:14:53,118
and kill those who deserve it.

1108
01:14:59,082 --> 01:15:01,168
What's with the last one?

1109
01:15:03,712 --> 01:15:05,255
I'm going to kill

1110
01:15:05,339 --> 01:15:07,424
every single scumbag who betrays

1111
01:15:07,508 --> 01:15:09,092
and stabs me in the back.

1112
01:15:11,136 --> 01:15:12,638
Think about this.

1113
01:15:12,721 --> 01:15:16,099
Even if I do commit murder,

1114
01:15:16,892 --> 01:15:20,687
I'll just need to attend trial
a few times before I die

1115
01:15:20,771 --> 01:15:22,064
in three months.

1116
01:15:24,358 --> 01:15:27,861
Right. You could be my attorney.

1117
01:15:32,199 --> 01:15:34,326
Okay, give me that. Let's go inside.

1118
01:15:35,410 --> 01:15:38,914
You have a knack
for saying such terrifying things.

1119
01:15:51,343 --> 01:15:52,427
Don't be afraid.

1120
01:15:54,096 --> 01:15:57,516
I know you would never betray me.

1121
01:15:59,268 --> 01:16:00,269
Of course not.

1122
01:16:00,352 --> 01:16:03,438
I'm not afraid.

1123
01:16:09,778 --> 01:16:10,696
By the way,

1124
01:16:12,281 --> 01:16:14,950
your phone was turned off.

1125
01:16:16,326 --> 01:16:17,327
Where is it?

1126
01:16:17,411 --> 01:16:18,412
Is it not in there?

1127
01:16:19,788 --> 01:16:20,914
Right.

1128
01:16:21,456 --> 01:16:22,833
I must've left it in the car.

1129
01:16:22,916 --> 01:16:23,917
In the car?

1130
01:16:25,377 --> 01:16:27,379
Go in first. I'll get your phone.

1131
01:16:32,634 --> 01:16:34,344
Mr. Oh, have you left? Where are you?

1132
01:16:34,970 --> 01:16:36,888
What? Here it is.

1133
01:16:44,104 --> 01:16:45,856
It was in my pocket.

1134
01:16:51,820 --> 01:16:53,614
What? It's turned off.

1135
01:17:00,329 --> 01:17:02,122
Hae-in, wait.

1136
01:17:32,903 --> 01:17:35,113
-What are you doing?
-I'm not sure.

1137
01:17:37,991 --> 01:17:39,034
What…

1138
01:17:39,826 --> 01:17:40,827
am I

1139
01:17:42,746 --> 01:17:43,789
doing right now?

1140
01:17:44,790 --> 01:17:45,832
I'm glad

1141
01:17:47,459 --> 01:17:48,460
that you found

1142
01:17:49,127 --> 01:17:50,170
your phone.

1143
01:17:51,463 --> 01:17:52,464
It could've been

1144
01:17:53,423 --> 01:17:54,675
a hassle to get it.

1145
01:18:01,390 --> 01:18:02,391
Why wasn't I…

1146
01:18:06,895 --> 01:18:08,105
confident?

1147
01:18:09,064 --> 01:18:10,232
What?

1148
01:18:11,775 --> 01:18:13,068
What did you say?

1149
01:18:22,828 --> 01:18:24,079
Right.

1150
01:18:31,211 --> 01:18:32,337
I told you, right?

1151
01:18:33,422 --> 01:18:34,381
I'm going to try

1152
01:18:35,799 --> 01:18:37,509
new things from now on.

1153
01:19:10,959 --> 01:19:13,503
SANSSOUCI PALACE, POTSDAM, GERMANY
THREE YEARS AGO

1154
01:19:22,763 --> 01:19:24,806
Did you say this place had no worries?

1155
01:19:26,683 --> 01:19:29,936
"Sans souci" in French
means "carefree."

1156
01:19:31,897 --> 01:19:33,398
That's just ridiculous.

1157
01:19:33,482 --> 01:19:35,066
How could such a place exist?

1158
01:19:36,234 --> 01:19:37,486
Do you know The Happy Prince?

1159
01:19:37,569 --> 01:19:41,114
The prince who made
a swallow poke out his eyes?

1160
01:19:44,034 --> 01:19:45,118
Yes.

1161
01:19:47,078 --> 01:19:49,831
The prince used to live in this palace.

1162
01:19:52,083 --> 01:19:54,503
I only realized one thing
after reading that book

1163
01:19:54,586 --> 01:19:55,921
as a child.

1164
01:19:56,004 --> 01:19:58,006
"You'll always suffer away from home."

1165
01:19:58,673 --> 01:20:01,134
Even the prince probably missed his home.

1166
01:20:01,218 --> 01:20:03,929
He left home only to suffer.

1167
01:20:04,012 --> 01:20:05,931
He gave away his gems and eyes.

1168
01:20:09,351 --> 01:20:10,560
Hae-in.

1169
01:20:13,313 --> 01:20:15,148
That's why he's the "happy prince."

1170
01:20:15,232 --> 01:20:18,443
Please. He wasn't happy.
He just changed before his death.

1171
01:20:19,152 --> 01:20:21,196
We should stay true to ourselves

1172
01:20:21,279 --> 01:20:23,698
and not act out of character
just because we're dying.

1173
01:20:42,008 --> 01:20:43,677
I'd like to build something.

1174
01:20:44,261 --> 01:20:46,471
A cancer support center
that aids employees' families.

1175
01:20:46,555 --> 01:20:47,722
Sorry?

1176
01:20:47,806 --> 01:20:50,892
You want to offer financial help
to their families?

1177
01:20:50,976 --> 01:20:52,018
Why?

1178
01:20:52,853 --> 01:20:54,062
For efficiency, of course.

1179
01:20:54,938 --> 01:20:56,439
What do you mean?

1180
01:20:56,523 --> 01:20:58,733
Imagine if your family member has cancer.

1181
01:20:58,817 --> 01:21:00,235
Could you focus on work?

1182
01:21:00,318 --> 01:21:02,571
-Probably not.
-Right?

1183
01:21:02,654 --> 01:21:05,323
Then you wouldn't be able
to sell your products.

1184
01:21:05,407 --> 01:21:06,741
That would be my loss.

1185
01:21:07,325 --> 01:21:10,579
And you'd cry in the toilet
about how you're in need of money.

1186
01:21:10,662 --> 01:21:12,706
Your makeup would run,
your eyes would be swollen.

1187
01:21:12,789 --> 01:21:15,667
It would only bring down
our department store's reputation.

1188
01:21:15,750 --> 01:21:17,878
I see.

1189
01:21:17,961 --> 01:21:18,920
I'm not trying

1190
01:21:19,671 --> 01:21:21,673
to help others out of goodwill.

1191
01:21:21,756 --> 01:21:25,719
It's all about the efficiency
and the financial aspect.

1192
01:21:29,055 --> 01:21:31,892
QUEEN OF TEARS

1193
01:22:00,128 --> 01:22:01,713
-Are you going to bed?
-Let's do it.

1194
01:22:01,796 --> 01:22:04,966
It was because I was scared.
That's why my heart was racing so much.

1195
01:22:05,050 --> 01:22:07,427
Now that I've been cured,

1196
01:22:07,510 --> 01:22:09,471
you're going to betray me?

1197
01:22:09,554 --> 01:22:10,847
Watch out!

1198
01:22:10,931 --> 01:22:12,933
What kind of lunatic yells like that here?

1199
01:22:13,975 --> 01:22:16,311
You're not the Eun-sung I knew.

1200
01:22:16,394 --> 01:22:18,772
I've worked very hard
to hear this from you.

1201
01:22:18,855 --> 01:22:21,942
I don't even like Hae-in.
Why would I be jealous?

1202
01:22:23,526 --> 01:22:25,153
I have something to tell you.

1203
01:22:25,236 --> 01:22:27,572
Don't worry.
It's good news that you'll love.

1204
01:22:31,743 --> 01:22:33,745
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim
